## Typography Rules

### Font families

```
--font-display  'Space Grotesk'  → H1, hero, display text
--font-heading  'Outfit'         → H2–H6, section titles
--font-body     'Inter'          → body copy, UI labels, buttons
--font-mono     'JetBrains Mono' → code, technical content
```

In Tailwind: `font-display`, `font-heading`, `font-body`, `font-mono`.

### Type scale

Use `--font-size-*` token variables in custom CSS, or Tailwind's `text-*` utilities (which map to the same tokens via `@theme inline`):

```
text-2xs  → 10px    text-4xl → 36px
text-xs   → 12px    text-5xl → 48px
text-sm   → 14px    text-6xl → 60px
text-base → 16px    text-7xl → 72px
text-lg   → 18px    text-8xl → 96px
text-xl   → 20px
text-2xl  → 24px
text-3xl  → 30px
```

### IMPORTANT: Never hardcode font sizes in px or rem directly. Use the scale.

---

## Spacing Rules

Use the 4px base spacing scale. In Tailwind, use standard `p-*`, `m-*`, `gap-*` utilities. In custom CSS, use `var(--space-*)`:

```
--space-1  = 4px    --space-8  = 32px   --space-24 = 96px
--space-2  = 8px    --space-10 = 40px   --space-32 = 128px
--space-3  = 12px   --space-12 = 48px   --space-40 = 160px
--space-4  = 16px   --space-16 = 64px
--space-6  = 24px   --space-20 = 80px
```

Named semantic spacers: `--section-y` (96px), `--section-x` (24px).

---

## Border Radius Rules

```
--radius-sm   4px    (tags, badges)
--radius-md   8px    (buttons, inputs)
--radius-lg   12px   (small cards)
--radius-xl   16px   (cards, panels)
--radius-2xl  24px   (large panels)
--radius-full 9999px (pills, avatars)
```

Component aliases: `--radius-btn`, `--radius-card`, `--radius-input`, `--radius-badge`.
In Tailwind: `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl`, `rounded-2xl`, `rounded-full`.

---

## Shadow & Glow Rules

Use token variables — never hardcode `box-shadow` values:

```
Depth:   --shadow-xs  --shadow-sm  --shadow-md  --shadow-lg  --shadow-xl  --shadow-2xl
Glow:    --glow-xs    --glow-sm    --glow-md    --glow-lg    --glow-xl
Text:    --glow-text-sm  --glow-text-md  --glow-text-lg
Cards:   --shadow-card  --shadow-card-hover  --shadow-card-accent
```

Tailwind utility classes: `.glow-xs`, `.glow-sm`, `.glow-md`, `.glow-lg`, `.glow-text-sm`, `.glow-text-md`.

---

## Transition Rules

```css
transition: opacity var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-default);
transition: transform var(--duration-slow) var(--ease-spring);
```

```
Durations: --duration-fast (150ms)  --duration-normal (250ms)
           --duration-slow (400ms)  --duration-slower (600ms)

Easings:   --ease-default  cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)
           --ease-in-out   cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)
           --ease-spring   cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)
```

---

## Component & File Conventions

- UI components: `src/app/components/ui/`
- Page sections: `src/app/pages/`
- Feature components: `src/app/components/`
- Styles: `src/styles/` (add to existing files; avoid new CSS files unless necessary)

### Component patterns

- All components accept a `className` prop for composition.
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes for layout and spacing.
- For complex or stateful styles, use CSS custom properties from the design system.
- Use `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` (`cn()`) for conditional class composition.
- IMPORTANT: Use Radix UI primitives from `src/app/components/ui/` before creating new ones.

---

## Glass Morphism

Use the utility classes from `src/styles/glass.css`:

```
.glass-ios        Basic dark glass (cards, surfaces)
.glass-premium    Stronger glass (featured sections)
.glass-card       Card glass with depth shadow
.glass-subtle     Minimal, nearly invisible glass
.glass-teal       Green-tinted glass (accent areas)
.glass-nav        Navigation bar glass
.glass-modal      Modal/overlay glass
.glass-input      Form input glass
```

IMPORTANT: Do not create new glass effects with hardcoded `rgba` values. Extend `glass.css` using token variables.

---

## Asset Rules

- Icons: use `lucide-react` (already installed). Do not install new icon packages.
- Images: use `.webp` format in `public/` or `src/assets/images/`.
- Videos: store in `public/videos/`.
- If Figma MCP returns a localhost source for an asset, use that source directly.
